Detailed Description

LockProvider represents the five lock states. A pointer to this provider can be retrieved from the main provider via the id:

c_lock_provider_id

Following column ids are defined: c_mcc_id :NumberType: c_mnc_id :NumberType: c_unlock_startup :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN c_unlock_menubased :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN c_unlock_keybased :NumberType: cast to BOOLEAN c_no_locks_id :NumberType: c_no_files :NumberType: c_cause_id :NumberType: cast to SecLockCause c_result_id :NumberType: cast to SecLockResult c_lock_type_id :NumberType: cast to SecLockType c_lock_status_id :NumberType: cast to SecLockStatus c_lock_result_id :NumberType: cast to SecLockResult c_lock_dcp_sup_id :NumberType: c_lock_retrial_method_id:NumberType: c_lock_retrial_count_id :NumberType: c_lock_time_id :NumberType: c_lock_order_id :NumberType:

This provider only consists of one fixed row.

NOTE: Please do not instantiate this class.
